"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1932265-why-do-olympic-athletes-bite-medals-reason-explained-after-tom-daley-chomp\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Sports fans may be taken aback to discover thatOlympicgold has not always been the ultimate prize in the Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 113, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sports fans\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 11}, {\"ngram\": \"the ultimate prize\", \"from\": 79, \"to\": 97}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 101, \"to\": 110}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the Olympics were revived in 1896, silver medals were initially given to champions.\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 132}, {\"ngram\": \"silver medals\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 168}, {\"ngram\": \"champions\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 202}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1904, however, they swapped silver for gold and have not looked back.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 277, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 242}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 251}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That said, gold medals have not been made entirely of the substance since 1912.\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 357, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 300}, {\"ngram\": \"the substance\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 345}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This makes sense given that each 529-gram medal would cost a whopping \\u00a330,000 to produce.\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sense\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 374}, {\"ngram\": \"each 529-gram medal\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The medals on offer in Paris, valued at around \\u00a3750, have just six grams of gold in them.\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 472, \"end\": 477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999541419139, \"rank\": 4.585809603943568e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The medals\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 459}, {\"ngram\": \"offer\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 468}, {\"ngram\": \"just six grams\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 521}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 529}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rest, ironically, is made out of silver, accounting for around 95 per cent of the medallion.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 635, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rest\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 547}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 582}, {\"ngram\": \"around 95 per cent\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 617}, {\"ngram\": \"the medallion\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 634}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When these medals are won, athletes have developed a habit of biting them while posing for photos.\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 735, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these medals\", \"from\": 642, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"a habit\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"photos\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 734}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the past, it was said this tradition stemmed from merchants who used to bite gold coins to test their purity (gold is a soft metal, so if teeth leave an indent the coin is pure), but this theory has since been debunked.\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 958, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 747}, {\"ngram\": \"this tradition\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 775}, {\"ngram\": \"merchants\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 798}, {\"ngram\": \"gold coins\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"their purity\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 847}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"a soft metal\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 869}, {\"ngram\": \"teeth\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 882}, {\"ngram\": \"an indent\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 898}, {\"ngram\": \"the coin\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 907}, {\"ngram\": \"this theory\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 933}]}, {\"sentence\": \"David Wallechinsky, president of the International Society of Olympic Historians, revealed in 2012 the actual reason why athletes seem eager to taste the medal they have worked so hard to win.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Wallechinsky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 989}, {\"ngram\": \"the International Society\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1018}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic Historians\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"the actual reason\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1089}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1119}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's become an obsession with the photographers,\\\" he told CNN.\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 0.9999998154987849, \"rank\": 1.3296057413510672e-07, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an obsession\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1178}, {\"ngram\": \"the photographers\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1201}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think they look at it as an iconic shot, as something that you can probably sell.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1302, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an iconic shot\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1274}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think it's something the athletes would probably do on their own.\\\"\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1378, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1345}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the origin of athletes biting their medals remains unclear, it's known that photographers often encourage them to do so for a memorable shot.\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1529, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the origin\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1398}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1410}, {\"ngram\": \"their medals\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"photographers\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1477}, {\"ngram\": \"a memorable shot\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1528}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This iconic pose, coupled with an athlete's newfound fame, makes for a perfect photo opportunity.\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1627, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This iconic pose\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete's newfound fame\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1587}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect photo opportunity\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1626}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Daley, Team GB's celebrated diver, has amassed a collection of medals throughout his career, including three bronze, one gold, and one silver.\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1629, \"end\": 1638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1912303418023454e-39, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}, {\"begin\": 1640, \"end\": 1647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9335193634034533, \"rank\": 0.07078848381892917, \"text\": \"Tea